        {
            "id": "default_values",
            "elements": [
                {
                    "type": "text",
                    "content": "You can give `__init__` parameters default values, making some attributes optional:"
                },
                {
                    "type": "code",
                    "content": "class Product:\n    def __init__(self, name, stock=0):\n        self.name = name\n        self.stock = stock\n\nproduct1 = Product(\"Laptop\")\nproduct2 = Product(\"Mouse\", 100)\n\nprint(product1.stock)\nprint(product2.stock)",
                    "properties": {
                        "language": "python",
                        "output": "0\n100"
                    }
                },
                {
                    "type": "text",
                    "content": "`stock` has a default of `0`, so you can create products without specifying stock. If you do provide stock, it uses that value instead."
                }
            ]
        },
